<tbody>
<row valign="top">
<entry valign="top" align="left"><list id="fs-idm245499440" list-type="bulleted">
<item>Utilizes external expertise, removes the need for in-house expertise</item>
<item>Frees up capacity for other uses</item>
<item>Frees up capital for other uses</item>
<item>Allows management to focus on competitive strengths</item>
<item>Transfers some production and technological risks to supplier</item>
</list></entry>
<entry valign="top" align="left"><list id="fs-idm236030512" list-type="bulleted">
<item>Takes away control over quality and timing of production</item>
<item>May limit ability to upsize or downsize production</item>
<item>May have hidden costs and/or a lack of stability of price</item>
<item>May diminish innovation</item>
<item>Often makes it difficult to bring the production back in-house once it has been removed</item>
</list></entry>
</row>
